Nat ROGAN, Collector of Internal Revenue, etc., Appellant, v. Dorothy Blanche MILLS, etc., Appellee. No. 8580. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. June 21, 1937. Peirson M. Hall, U. S. Atty., and Alva C. Baird, both of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Sloane & Steiner, of San Diego, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, DENMAN, and MATPIEWS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of appellant and good cause therefor appearing, ordered appeal in above cause dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and the mandate of this court issue forthwith.
